It checks if the opc is LUSTRE_OPC_CREATE to decide if to parse the file name and decode the mds #.

Patch Set 1:

Instrad of changing ll_mknod() why not just call ll_new_node() with LUSTRE_OPC_CREATE from ll_create_nd(). This solves avoids the leaked files from mknod() problem.


diff --git a/lustre/llite/namei.c b/lustre/llite/namei.c
index b687d6e..1d1eba7 100644
--- a/lustre/llite/namei.c
+++ b/lustre/llite/namei.c
@@ -1162,7 +1162,8 @@ static int ll_create_nd(struct inode *dir, struct dentry *dentry,
                it = lld->lld_it;

         if (!it)
-               return ll_mknod(dir, dentry, mode, 0);
+               return ll_new_node(dir, dentry, NULL, mode, 0,
+                                  LUSTRE_OPC_CREATE);

        lld->lld_it = NULL;
